==English==

===Alternative spellings===
* [[stanch]]

===Pronunciation===
* {{AHD|stônch, stänch}}

===Etymology===
{{OF.}} ''estanchier'', stanch, from Vulgar Latin ''stanticāre'', stop, from Latin ''stāre'', stand
  
===Adjective===
{{en-adj|er}}

# [[loyal]], [[trustworthy]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|staunch|es}}

#{{transitive}} To stop the flow of (blood).
#{{transitive}} To check the flow of.

====Translations====
*Bosnian [[zaustaviti]] (protok nečega, npr. krvi, suza, i sl.), ''inf''

===Usage note===
The spelling ''staunch'' is more commonly used for the adjective. In contrast, ''[[stanch]]'' is more commonly used as the spelling of the verb.

